10 An Act relating to agriculture; amending 2 O.S. 2021,
Section 10-78, which relates to the sale of eggs;
11 allowing for sale of certain eggs in specified
locations; establishing limit on sale of ungraded
12 eggs; and providing an effective date.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 2 O.S. 2021, Section 10-78, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 10-78. A. Oklahoma producers of eggs selling ungraded
19 eggs from their own flock production are exempt from this
20 subarticle. Nothing in this subarticle shall prohibit the sale of
21 eggs produced on the farm and sold direct to the consumer on the
22 farm, at a farmers’ market, or otherwise off the farm direct to the
23 consumer. Eggs sold under this section shall be produced by hens
24 maintained on the farm from which the eggs are sold.
SB2110 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 B. To be eligible to sell ungraded eggs pursuant to the
2 provisions of subsection A of this section, an egg producer in this
3 state shall be limited to the sale of no more than one hundred fifty
4 (150) dozen eggs per month.
5 C. A producer may sell graded eggs if in compliance with this
6 subarticle.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
8
9 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON ENERGY AND NATURAL RESOURCES
OVERSIGHT, dated 04/13/2026 - DO PASS.
